Top Reviews Snippet: this is the worst activity i've ever done, and yet i love karting! there are several problems: - the staff is rude, from the woman at reception to the two tough guys at the track. it's bordering on racism for these three people. - the hygiene, with helmets that smell bad, like the protections, probably not washed since the opening. - the equipment, beyond the smell, how can you rent helmets in such poor condition and without visors (when it's raining)! the karts are dirty, old, and don't last a full round, in my opinion... - safety: no explanations (i'm not a karting expert), no safety videos, and no one is there if you have a problem on the track; they're tapping away on their smartphones at the reception bar! - the track: it was laid out blindly, and it's pointless. - the price: ‚Ç¨25 per round. there were two of us, practically the only customers of the evening. we each bought two games. due to torrential rain at the end of the first game, we couldn't play the second game. they refused a refund. only credit notes are accepted. but when the equipment is rubbish, the reception is disgusting, the rain is unstoppable, and we're the only customers, you can do something for people who won't be back in martinique for years! or at least pretend to be polite. the experience ended with death threats from the lady at the reception!  in short... avoid! luckily for them, they have no competition. | very nice, there are also two-seater karts for couples or parents/children. 25 or 30 for 10 minutes. the track is nice, with the possibility of overtaking on most corners. the overall area outside the track lacks any lively amenities. there are quite a few seats, but it's not very conducive to enjoying the atmosphere. | the circuit is really good and enjoyable, but i find the time on the track too short for the price, which is quite high. the restrooms are unfortunately unsanitary, to the point that i prefer not to use them when i come here, which is a shame for a place like this.  the staff are okay. generally, they do their job well and aren't unpleasant, although i've encountered a few less-than-friendly employees. overall, it's a good experience, but there are definitely areas for improvement, especially regarding hygiene and value for money.

Name: Simaho Nautique
Top Reviews Snippet: we were eight friends aboard pia, a lagoon 440 catamaran, for a week-long cruise around guadeloupe in january 2025. thomas, the shipseo sales representative, was very helpful and responsive in handling our reservation. while waiting for our trip, we contacted him again with various questions, all of which he answered, even though we had to follow up with him at times. the boat was well-equipped and comfortable. the four cabins had a bathroom and toilet, which was very much appreciated. the only area for improvement was the boat's condition, which was slightly below what the photos available on their website suggest. jessica, our skipper, provided excellent advice on the route and anchorages. she perfectly managed the navigation, which was made difficult by the rough seas, strong winds, and squalls we unfortunately encountered during our trip. she agreed to let us participate in the maneuvers and demonstrated remarkable precision during the various dockings. we will have wonderful memories of this stay aboard pia, piloted by jessica. thank you to the shipseo team. | if you're looking for a real adventure, then let's go!  we chose to explore the grenadines aboard the famous ylang ylang: if you're looking for authenticity, adventure, and discovery, i highly recommend it! thanks to our skipper, we discovered anchorages far from mass tourism. certainly more unusual and wild, but much more immersive in the local culture! the boat is perfect for learning the basics of sailing; it's a bit old-fashioned but still very efficient in terms of navigation. i recommend cruises with shipseo; their expertise and experience at sea make these holidays incredibly enriching and provide a complete escape from your daily routine. next up: brittany! | there are some unforgettable vacations that stay with you for life: and this one, spent aboard pia, discovering the grenadines, will remain etched in our memories forever!  everything was seamless, from start to finish. we were accommodating, adapting at any moment. we even had to make a few changes to suit our needs; which was never a problem.  leaving le marin in martinique, heading for the grenadines for 9 days: a boat admirably skippered by nicolas, who knows and masters the area, the islands, the anchorages... and what can i say about claire's delicious meals: the joy of sitting down at the table, without having to worry about meals or the fridge: that's what a real vacation is, pure bliss!  like some of the comments, let me tell you, those of you reading these lines who are still hesitating, that you can book with complete peace of mind; you won't be disappointed with your stay. available, friendly, adaptable, able to step aside when necessary, always offering good advice... don't hesitate, for a successful vacation in the grenadines with a skipper and hostess.  happy sailing! Top Reviews Snippet: booking, payment, and account creation are all done online, which is very convenient.  upon arrival, a briefing is given via video screen in a small room, and then the game begins. as soon as you put on the virtual reality headset, the immersion is total. while everyone is getting equipped, you're already immersed in a virtual waiting world, which immediately sets the mood. the game then starts, with complete immersion: at the beginning of each match and each round, you can choose and change your weapon. you can see the number of cartridges remaining in your weapon, as well as your health bar displayed on your left arm, which further enhances immersion and the game's clarity. the game itself lasts approximately 25 to 30 minutes, a well-paced format.  we played the cooperative mode, where you face waves of enemies as a team, which works very well and reinforces the collaborative aspect.  there's also another game mode, but it can become a bit repetitive over time. in this respect, adding new maps would definitely be a big plus to keep the experience fresh. the sense of depth, and even height‚Äîespecially when walking on a walkway‚Äîis truly impressive. the graphics are decent overall, even if they're not on par with the latest pc or console games. two areas for improvement, in my opinion: headphones for total sound immersion, as you can sometimes hear people nearby in the real world, with a slight delay compared to the game; weapon vibrations to further enhance immersion. in the end: an experience definitely worth repeating! | the activities were great, and the staff were fantastic too üëç ‚Ä¶ | a great experience, definitely worth trying! üòÅüòÅ very welcoming and the staff are fantastic. ‚Ä¶

Top Reviews Snippet: after reading all the reviews (many negative ones too), i decided to go and see for myself. i did three heats in adult karts with my son (12 years old, over 160cm). the karts were in reasonable technical condition. occasionally, there was a rattle or a steering wheel that was slightly askew. but they all pulled along nicely. the food and drinks were very affordable. a generous plate of fries and a decent-sized cup of coffee were included. the staff were all very friendly and helpful. during races with 10/12 karts on the track, several track marshals were active and kept a close eye on things (contrary to what some reviews suggest). the blue flags were followed fairly well by others, although this of course partly depends on your fellow drivers. the track is technically challenging, with lots of fun corners. the upper level runs on a wooden floor, which can be a bit slippery at times. a nice challenge. unfortunately, the track is somewhat narrow, which makes overtaking a bit difficult at times.  all in all, a fun experience. and 30 minutes of karting for ‚Ç¨50 was great. and these karts run smoothly on lpg instead of electric. that's a much better experience! | it was actually more challenging than expected. it's a pretty cool track, especially if you're new to it. i thought the karts drove pretty well too. 10 minutes is quite a challenge to stay sharp, as the steering is heavy. my son and i also had a few bruises from hitting the barriers on the straight, but it didn't spoil the fun; it was really fun. the blue lights and flags work quite well, which is also nice because overtaking is difficult otherwise, and you don't really have to make a mistake. | great kart track with two levels! wide selection of helmets in many different sizes! delicious fries! the karts work perfectly; i've been there twice already.

Top Reviews Snippet: great place felt safe raced with other drivers all gear supplied | i know what you're asking when you see those four stars up there: "why not five, man? what could possibly knock your karting experience down from the lofty heights of internet ratings perfection to something a bit less eye-catching, to merely 'good' when so many other discerning individuals thought that their respective times were 'great, just really, really great' or whatever?" well, dear review-reader, i must say that whilst i had an absolute whale of a time in my allotted racing vehicle, and the price was pretty reasonable at a mere 29 pounds for my 2 consecutive 15 minute sessions of group racing fun, the only, rather minor niggles i had were with the condition of the facility's race track and the safety equipment on offer. the track badly needs a resurfacing to reduce the instances of coccyx complications you will contend with here, and the helmets, gloves and overalls certainly seem to have seen better days. it gives the whole place a slightly gymcrack (is that how you spell it?) feel, uncommensurate  with terms like 'your safety is our utmost concern'. if you are normal and do not fret about this trifling sort of thing, then pop on down and get your karting kicks at the anglia karting centre. it's likely far more interesting than whatever else you would otherwise be up to. the staff are friendly and helpful, the karts go pretty well, the timing printouts you get are great if you're into competitive corporate bonding days or you just like numbers that tell you if you're a good or bad person and, bumpy approach notwithstanding, it was pretty easy to find due to a bigish sign by the road side. | amazing place for your kids to learn the ropes of karting

Top Reviews Snippet: why does glan y gors karting (gyg) deserve 5 stars. well lots of reasons. i agree wholeheartedly with red bull that it is one of the best kart tracks in the uk. it is long, fast flowing and quite ‚Äòtechnical‚Äô in places so challenging for all and a fantastic experience for both novice and seasoned karters alike. but you should know that as an outdoor track any session could be damp, wet or dry ‚Äì each with their own challenges. this means every session will be different. the track is in wales so. anything can happen with the weather ‚Äì it even snows sometimes. for obvious reasons that might mean a session has to be cancelled but that is pretty rare ‚Äì usually whatever the weather you can go racing . it doesn‚Äôt matter if the rain is heavy, or you have to wipe the hail off your visor, or because of a mist you can‚Äôt see  other parts of the circuit. the sun can be bright too ‚Äì quite fantastic. apart from the track you should know that it is a family run business that really cares about its customers. the reception, catering and track staff are all first class. so apart from the care and attention you get what you should know is that gyg really does care. most importantly you should know that you are not treated as a ‚Äòcash cow‚Äô as happens at some other tracks i could name. i don‚Äôt use their kit, as i have my own, but they do provide everything you need which is in good order ‚Äì from well-maintained karts to race wear. both these things can be found wanting in other places. | been on a test day with my son, he thoroughly enjoyed the day and has already marked the next date in the calendar | brilliant circuit
